      "writtenOn": "2017-10-03T02:53:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done, I added a bunch of comments detailing the threading expectations, throughout.  I also changed this method to return an RAII \"ScopedEglContext\" object that will automatically unset the context and reduce the possibility of misuse.\n\nThis can be called on any thread, but unset must be called on the same thread, and callers must be resilient to having their EGL state reset on that thread-- either by not performing other GL rendering or by setting it back.",
